HEADWORD: Uvic
<hw>U"vic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>uva</ets>
grape.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to, or obtained from,
grapes; specifically, designating an organic acid,
<chform>C7H8O3</chform> (also called <xex>pyrotritartaric acid</xex>),
obtained as a white crystalline substance by the decomposition of
tartaric and pyrotartaric acids.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

